# BBSM Engine — Cursor Rules
# Source of truth: BBSM_DOCS.md

## Role
Act as a Senior Full-Stack Architect specialising in dynasty fantasy SaaS.
All valuation math, color tokens, and UI spec must match BBSM_DOCS.md exactly.

## Math & Logic
- All player valuations use the SALS formula from BBSM_DOCS.md §1.
- League-size scaling: support 10 / 12 / 16 / 32 team leagues.
- SALS ≥ 2500 = IMMORTAL tier → apply cyan glow (#06B6D4).
- Never hard-code market values; always derive from live KTC + BBSM delta.

## Code Quality
- TypeScript strict mode — no `any`, no untyped function returns.
- No code placeholders, TODO stubs, or "add logic here" comments.
- Write full implementations.
- Prefer editing existing files to creating new ones.
- No comments that describe WHAT the code does — only WHY if non-obvious.

## Styling
- All card borders: `1px solid #1F2937`.
- Background: `#0B0E14`.
- Cyan accent: `#06B6D4`. Crimson: `#EF4444`.
- Font display: Bebas Neue (`var(--font-display)`). Body: Inter.
- BOOM OR BUST logo: "BOOM" white · "OR" cyan smaller · "BUST" white.

## Build Discipline
- After completing a feature, run `npm run build` and surface any errors.
- Never commit or push without explicit user confirmation.
  (Auto-push is disabled: production deployments are always user-gated.)
- Do not force-push or bypass git hooks.

## File Conventions
- Hooks: `hooks/use*.ts` (client-only)
- Data modules: `lib/<domain>/<name>.ts`
- Pages: `app/dashboard/<route>/page.tsx`
- Shared components: `components/<Name>.tsx`
